
Overview of noun platoon

The noun platoon has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (6) platoon -- (a military unit that is a subdivision of a company; usually has a headquarters and two or more squads; usually commanded by a lieutenant)
2. (2) platoon -- (a team of policemen working under the military platoon system)
3. platoon -- (a group of persons who are engaged in a common activity; "platoons of tourists poured out of the busses"; "the defensive platoon of the football team")
